[2] Cholera - Angola
Date: Tue, 8 Aug 2006
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Government of Angola Press [edited]
<http://www.reliefweb.int/rw/RWB.NSF/db900SID/SODA-6SH32F?OpenDocument>

Angola's Health Ministry registered from 5 to 6 Aug 2006, 51 cases of
cholera and one death, in 8 of the 15 provinces that are affected by
the disease since Feb 2006.
Angola Press learned from a document about the epidemic disease that,
the new cases were detected in the provinces of Uige, the most
affected during this period with 20 cases, Bengo (3), Benguela (4),
Kwanza Norte (1), Kwanza Sul (5), Luanda (11), Kuando Kubango (3) and
Namibe (4). Statistical information of the sector show that last week
335 cases with 18 deaths were registered (12 in hospitals and the
remaining 6 away from hospitals), corresponding to a 5.4 percent
death rate.
In the above-mentioned period Uige province registered the highest
incidence and deaths with 147 cases that claimed 7 lives.
From 13 Feb to 6 Aug 2006, the Health Ministry detected 51 700 cases
of cholera that resulted in 2156 deaths.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[A map of Angola showing the location of the provinces can be found
at <http://www.un.org/Depts/Cartographic/map/profile/angola.pdf>. The
only 3 provinces yet to be reported involved are Cunene, Moxico, and
Lunda Sul. They also can be found on the map. - Mod.LL]
