[3] Cholera, diarrhea - India (Punjab)
Date: Tue, 8 Aug 2006
From: ProMED-mail promed@promedmail.org
Source: Punjab Newsline [edited]
<http://www.punjabnewsline.com/content/view/1152/38/>

Tibba Village in Nurpur Bedi area of Ropar district is in the grip of
cholera and gastroenteritis. According to information more than 100
residents of the village have been found to be suffering from
diarrhea. Two persons were found to be affected with cholera.
The diseases said to have been spread due to leakage of the water
supply pipe in the village. The residents have reportedly started
complaining of diarrhea about week ago. However, the number of
patients started increasing day before yesterday. About 50 patient
have visited government dispensary at village Tibba-Tapprian for
treatment while others have got treatment from private hospitals.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[A map of India showing the northwestern state of Punjab can be found
at:
<http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Image:India_Punjab_locator_map.svg>.
Ropar district is in the extreme central eastern area of the state. -
